Belgium-born Madeleine De Blic, another Pondicherry resident and founder of Volontariat India who has been selected for the Padma Shri award in the field of social work, felt her work for the poor and the needy had been recognised. “Although I was born in Belgium, I consider India as my country. An award given by the Indian government and people is more close to my heart,” Ms. Blic said.French honourMs. De Blic was awarded the title of Chevalier de la Légion d’Honneur for her work in 2013. Volontariat runs a home for street and destitute Children, a home for the aged and a vocational training centre.- Staff Reporter